24// We use this constant internally to signal that a module has requested
25// a callback right away. When this is set, no call to TimeUntilNextProcess
26// should be made, but Process() should be called directly.
27const int64_t kCallProcessImmediately = -1;
28
29int64_t GetNextCallbackTime(Module* module, int64_t time_now) {
30 int64_t interval = module->TimeUntilNextProcess();
31 if (interval < 0) {
32 // Falling behind, we should call the callback now.
33 return time_now;
34 }
35 return time_now + interval;
36}
37} // namespace
38
39ProcessThread::~ProcessThread() {}
40
41// static
42std::unique_ptr<ProcessThread> ProcessThread::Create(const char* thread_name) {
43 return std::unique_ptr<ProcessThread>(new ProcessThreadImpl(thread_name));
44}
45
46ProcessThreadImpl::ProcessThreadImpl(const char* thread_name)
47 : stop_(false), thread_name_(thread_name) {}
48
49ProcessThreadImpl::~ProcessThreadImpl() {
50 RTC_DCHECK(thread_checker_.IsCurrent());
51 RTC_DCHECK(!stop_);
52
53 while (!delayed_tasks_.empty()) {
54 delete delayed_tasks_.top().task;
55 delayed_tasks_.pop();
56 }
57
58 while (!queue_.empty()) {
59 delete queue_.front();
60 queue_.pop();
61 }
62}
63
64void ProcessThreadImpl::Delete() {
65 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Process thread " << thread_name_
66 << " is destroyed as a TaskQueue.";
67 Stop();
68 delete this;
69}
70
71// Doesn't need locking, because the contending thread isn't running.
72void ProcessThreadImpl::Start() RTC_NO_THREAD_SAFETY_ANALYSIS {
73 RTC_DCHECK(thread_checker_.IsCurrent());
74 RTC_DCHECK(thread_.empty());
75 if (!thread_.empty())
76 return;
77
78 RTC_DCHECK(!stop_);
79
80 for (ModuleCallback& m : modules_)
81 m.module->ProcessThreadAttached(this);
82
83 thread_ = rtc::PlatformThread::SpawnJoinable(
84 [this] {
85 CurrentTaskQueueSetter set_current(this);
86 while (Process()) {
87 }
88 },
89 thread_name_);
90}
91
92void ProcessThreadImpl::Stop() {
93 RTC_DCHECK(thread_checker_.IsCurrent());
94 if (thread_.empty())
95 return;
96
97 {
98 // Need to take lock, for synchronization with `thread_`.
99 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
100 stop_ = true;
101 }
102
103 wake_up_.Set();
104 thread_.Finalize();
105
106 StopNoLocks();
107}
108
109// No locking needed, since this is called after the contending thread is
110// stopped.
111void ProcessThreadImpl::StopNoLocks() RTC_NO_THREAD_SAFETY_ANALYSIS {
112 RTC_DCHECK(thread_.empty());
113 stop_ = false;
114
115 for (ModuleCallback& m : modules_)
116 m.module->ProcessThreadAttached(nullptr);
117}
118
119void ProcessThreadImpl::WakeUp(Module* module) {
120 // Allowed to be called on any thread.
121 auto holds_mutex = [this] {
122 if (!IsCurrent()) {
123 return false;
124 }
125 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(this);
126 return holds_mutex_;
127 };
128 if (holds_mutex()) {
129 // Avoid locking if called on the ProcessThread, via a module's Process),
130 WakeUpNoLocks(module);
131 } else {
132 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
133 WakeUpInternal(module);
134 }
135 wake_up_.Set();
136}
137
138// Must be called only indirectly from Process, which already holds the lock.
139void ProcessThreadImpl::WakeUpNoLocks(Module* module)
140 RTC_NO_THREAD_SAFETY_ANALYSIS {
141 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(this);
142 WakeUpInternal(module);
143}
144
145void ProcessThreadImpl::WakeUpInternal(Module* module) {
146 for (ModuleCallback& m : modules_) {
147 if (m.module == module)
148 m.next_callback = kCallProcessImmediately;
149 }
150}
151
152void ProcessThreadImpl::PostTask(std::unique_ptr<QueuedTask> task) {
153 // Allowed to be called on any thread, except from a module's Process method.
154 if (IsCurrent()) {
155 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(this);
156 RTC_DCHECK(!holds_mutex_) << "Calling ProcessThread::PostTask from "
157 "Module::Process is not supported";
158 }
159 {
160 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
161 queue_.push(task.release());
162 }
163 wake_up_.Set();
164}
165
166void ProcessThreadImpl::PostDelayedTask(std::unique_ptr<QueuedTask> task,
167 uint32_t milliseconds) {
168 int64_t run_at_ms = rtc::TimeMillis() + milliseconds;
169 bool recalculate_wakeup_time;
170 {
171 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
172 recalculate_wakeup_time =
173 delayed_tasks_.empty() || run_at_ms < delayed_tasks_.top().run_at_ms;
174 delayed_tasks_.emplace(run_at_ms, std::move(task));
175 }
176 if (recalculate_wakeup_time) {
177 wake_up_.Set();
178 }
179}
180
181void ProcessThreadImpl::RegisterModule(Module* module,
182 const rtc::Location& from) {
183 RTC_DCHECK(thread_checker_.IsCurrent());
184 RTC_DCHECK(module) << from.ToString();
185
186#if RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON
187 {
188 // Catch programmer error.
189 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
190 for (const ModuleCallback& mc : modules_) {
191 RTC_DCHECK(mc.module != module)
192 << "Already registered here: " << mc.location.ToString()
193 << "\n"
194 "Now attempting from here: "
195 << from.ToString();
196 }
197 }
198#endif
199
200 // Now that we know the module isn't in the list, we'll call out to notify
201 // the module that it's attached to the worker thread. We don't hold
202 // the lock while we make this call.
203 if (!thread_.empty())
204 module->ProcessThreadAttached(this);
205
206 {
207 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
208 modules_.push_back(ModuleCallback(module, from));
209 }
210
211 // Wake the thread calling ProcessThreadImpl::Process() to update the
212 // waiting time. The waiting time for the just registered module may be
213 // shorter than all other registered modules.
214 wake_up_.Set();
215}
216
217void ProcessThreadImpl::DeRegisterModule(Module* module) {
218 RTC_DCHECK(thread_checker_.IsCurrent());
219 RTC_DCHECK(module);
220
221 {
222 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
223 modules_.remove_if(
224 [&module](const ModuleCallback& m) { return m.module == module; });
225 }
226
227 // Notify the module that it's been detached.
228 module->ProcessThreadAttached(nullptr);
229}
230
231bool ProcessThreadImpl::Process() {
232 TRACE_EVENT1("webrtc", "ProcessThreadImpl", "name", thread_name_);
233 int64_t now = rtc::TimeMillis();
234 int64_t next_checkpoint = now + (1000 * 60);
235 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(this);
236 {
237 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
238 if (stop_)
239 return false;
240 for (ModuleCallback& m : modules_) {
241 // TODO(tommi): Would be good to measure the time TimeUntilNextProcess
242 // takes and dcheck if it takes too long (e.g. >=10ms). Ideally this
243 // operation should not require taking a lock, so querying all modules
244 // should run in a matter of nanoseconds.
245 if (m.next_callback == 0)
246 m.next_callback = GetNextCallbackTime(m.module, now);
247
248 // Set to true for the duration of the calls to modules' Process().
249 holds_mutex_ = true;
250 if (m.next_callback <= now ||
251 m.next_callback == kCallProcessImmediately) {
252 {
253 TRACE_EVENT2("webrtc", "ModuleProcess", "function",
254 m.location.function_name(), "file",
255 m.location.file_name());
256 m.module->Process();
257 }
258 // Use a new 'now' reference to calculate when the next callback
259 // should occur. We'll continue to use 'now' above for the baseline
260 // of calculating how long we should wait, to reduce variance.
261 int64_t new_now = rtc::TimeMillis();
262 m.next_callback = GetNextCallbackTime(m.module, new_now);
263 }
264 holds_mutex_ = false;
265
266 if (m.next_callback < next_checkpoint)
267 next_checkpoint = m.next_callback;
268 }
269
270 while (!delayed_tasks_.empty() && delayed_tasks_.top().run_at_ms <= now) {
271 queue_.push(delayed_tasks_.top().task);
272 delayed_tasks_.pop();
273 }
274
275 if (!delayed_tasks_.empty()) {
276 next_checkpoint =
277 std::min(next_checkpoint, delayed_tasks_.top().run_at_ms);
278 }
279
280 while (!queue_.empty()) {
281 QueuedTask* task = queue_.front();
282 queue_.pop();
283 mutex_.Unlock();
284 if (task->Run()) {
285 delete task;
286 }
287 mutex_.Lock();
288 }
289 }
290
291 int64_t time_to_wait = next_checkpoint - rtc::TimeMillis();
292 if (time_to_wait > 0)
293 wake_up_.Wait(static_cast<int>(time_to_wait));
294
295 return true;
296}
